<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-25T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-25T05:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4094: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-25T11:00:00+01:00">June 25, 1931—11 a.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 25—7:14
                                        a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>53. Department’s 34 [<hi rend="italic">37?</hi>], June 24, 11
                                        p.m.<note n="59" xml:id="d118fn59">Not printed.</note> Does
                                    the President’s proposal apply to Belgium equally as to France
                                    or is Belgium not to be considered as one of the “important
                                    creditor countries” who are to postpone debt and reparations
                                    receipts for one year.</p>
                                <p>If the latter is the case suggest I be given immediate
                                    authorization so to inform Foreign Office. Urgent reply by
                                    telegraph respectfully requested.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>